parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks from Engine and Transmission
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause damage to the engine and transmission, leading to premature wear and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the lower left-hand side of the engine and transmission
oil dripping from the seam where the engine and transmission are bolted together.

vehicle stalls after being restarted and idles at 4
000 RPM
throttle pulls cause the vehicle to completely shut off.

backfires and runs rough when overheated
noise in 5th gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compensator sprocket can cause the primary chain to lock up, leading to sudden loss of power and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Noise on the left side of the primary cover
vibration in 5th and 6th gear
transmission whine in 5th gear
clanking noise when shifting from 5th to 6th gear
sudden loss of power
primary chain locking up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire cracking and failure can lead to sudden loss of air pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks on the tire surface
tire blowout
loss of air pressure
difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering mechanism can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the rider is unable to steer the motorcycle.
symptoms: The handlebars rotate downward around the gas tank
making it impossible to steer the motorcycle left or right
excessive wobbling of the front end
difficulty operating the steering
rear of the vehicle steering out of the lane on its own.
